			<h1>7 - Hi Fi</h1>
			<p>I found from the people I talked to that people looked at phone bills for one main reason. They want to know if the amount of phone/sms/data they are using are exceeding what is included in their plan. If it doesn't, they don't really need more information. If it does, they want to be able to drill down to find out what/who is responsible for it.</p>

			<p>Based on that feedback, I made several major changes to the content that is immediately visible.</p>

			<p>I felt that tables implied that all information there were equally important, but it is not true in this context. If the goal was to find out what was costing the most minutes, obviously the most salient information should be the duration of the longest calls.</p>
			<p>Also, large tables do not scale very well on mobile devices, so I wanted a way to chunk key information more tightly.</p>
			
